{"entity": "Sandbox", "type": "concept", "description": "Sandbox is a program period during which FE operates from IFSC and is part of the implementation phase.<SEP>Sandbox is a testing environment where FinTech firms can test their solutions in isolation from the live market using data provided by regulated entities in the IFSC.<SEP>Sandbox is a controlled testing environment used to evaluate the FinTech Solution, outlining test criteria, expected outcomes, and success indicators.<SEP>Regulatory sandbox for testing fintech activities under the FinTech Entity Framework.<SEP>Sandbox is a controlled testing environment for FinTech entities to trial products under regulatory supervision as part of the FE Framework."}
