{"entity": "IFSC", "type": "location", "description": "International Financial Services Centre (IFSC) is a designated free‑zone jurisdiction situated in GIFT City, India, created to promote the growth of financial services and FinTech activities.  Regulated by the Indian Financial Services Regulatory Authority (IFSCA), the IFSC provides a structured regulatory environment for finance companies, finance units, and ancillary financial intermediaries.  Within this framework, entities can establish a branch or maintain a presence, obtain licensing, and conduct sandbox testing, accelerator programmes, and other special regulatory initiatives under a controlled setting.\n\nThe IFSC serves as an infrastructure hub that streamlines registration and licensing for FinTech firms and offers a locus for the deployment of regulatory sandboxes, allowing participants to pilot new products while ensuring compliance with industry standards.  Accelerator grants and additional incentives are administered through the IFSC, facilitating rapid scaling of technology‑driven financial solutions.\n\nAlthough commonly referred to as the “International Financial Services Centre,” the term IFSC also encompasses the Indian designation “Indian Financial Services Centre,” reflecting its role as a financial services free zone within India.  In this sense, the IFSC is a pivotal mechanism for consolidating regulatory oversight, fostering innovation, and positioning Indian FinTech firms on the global stage."}
