{"entity": "FinTech Entity", "type": "organization", "description": "FinTech Entity is a regulatory classification used by the Authority to describe an organization—domestic or foreign—that offers technologically enabled financial services or solutions. Such an entity is authorized by the Authority to operate FinTech services under the established framework and must meet applicable regulatory standards. A FinTech Entity is typically an applicant organization that seeks permission to develop, test, and launch its proposed solutions within the Industry Financial Services Cluster (IFSC) sandbox, operating under the jurisdiction of the Institute of Financial Services and Capital Markets Authority (IFSCA). In this capacity, the entity develops and tests new FinTech solutions in a controlled environment, with oversight provided by IFSCA to ensure compliance with industry rules and consumer protection. The designation of “FinTech Entity” signifies eligibility to apply under the FinTech Entity Framework and indicates that the company has obtained the necessary authorization to conduct business within the IFSC while adhering to regulatory requirements.<SEP>A FinTech entity is an organization authorized under the FE Framework that seeks incentives from the scheme.<SEP>A FinTech Entity is an entity authorized under specific circulars to provide technology-enabled financial services within the International Financial Services Centres."}
